# Deployment

Security Onion was installed in Standalone mode inside VirtualBox.

The web interface is accessible securely over HTTPS.

---

# Major Challenges

This deployment required extensive troubleshooting.

Issues encountered included:

- Host-Only networking configuration
- VirtualBox adapter configuration
- Container startup verification
- Management IP changes
- HTTPS connectivity
- Browser access
- Docker health monitoring
- Highstate synchronization
- Remote access configuration

One major issue occurred after changing the management IP from:

192.168.120.130

to

192.168.120.150

The web interface continued redirecting to the old IP address.

This was resolved using:

```
sudo so-ip-update
```

followed by a system reboot and verification of all containers.

---

# Remote Access

Security Onion is securely accessible remotely using Tailscale without exposing public ports.

This provides encrypted Zero Trust remote administration from trusted devices.

